1
00:00:01,793 --> 00:00:03,670
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:27,879
-[Soichiro] What?
-[man groaning]

3
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:30,716
I don't believe this.
Another 23 victims yesterday?

4
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:31,883
Are these confirmed?

5
00:01:32,009 --> 00:01:35,178
[L] As soon as we began to suspect
that Kira might be a student,

6
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:38,640
the pacing of the killings changed,
as if to contradict that theory.

7
00:01:38,724 --> 00:01:42,394
This can only mean that Kira has access
to police information.

8
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:45,188
[Light] When L discovers that I'm somehow
getting confidential information,

9
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:49,318
he'll be obligated to start investigating
the police to find the source of the leak.

10
00:01:49,443 --> 00:01:51,486
You're being followed by another human.

11
00:01:51,612 --> 00:01:53,113
He's watching you right now.

12
00:01:53,697 --> 00:01:54,990
[Light] That's a problem.

13
00:01:55,365 --> 00:01:58,118
I'll have to get rid of him
as soon as possible.

14
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:00,579
Because through a Shinigami's eyes,

15
00:02:00,662 --> 00:02:03,040
a human's name can be seen
above their head.

16
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:05,000
Not only that.
We see their lifespan as well.

17
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:06,001
LIGHT YAGAMI

18
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:09,880
However, if a Shinigami drops
his Death Note and a human picks it up,

19
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:13,050
he can grant that human
the eyes of a Shinigami.

20
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:16,261
The price for having a Shinigami's eyes...

21
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:19,181
is half of that person's
remaining lifespan.

22
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:20,307
That's all it is.

23
00:02:22,184 --> 00:02:25,312
So, what'll it be, Light? Is it a deal?

24
00:02:25,418 --> 00:02:28,315
PURSUIT

25
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:31,568
Has anyone seen Ryuk around lately.

26
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:34,655
Maybe he was serious
about losing his Death Note.

27
00:02:34,738 --> 00:02:37,866
It was probably picked up by some human
before he could get to it.

28
00:02:37,949 --> 00:02:41,203
No way. Then he'd be stuck there
till the end of that human's life

29
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:43,038
or until the Death Note is destroyed.

30
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,581
That could take a while.

31
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:48,669
Yeah, I can't picture
Ryuk doing something so boring.

32
00:02:48,752 --> 00:02:52,964
But you know what? I actually heard
he was carrying two Death Notes.

33
00:02:53,090 --> 00:02:55,634
[Shinigami] Seriously?
Why would he need two?

34
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:58,178
Beats me. I'll never understand that guy.

35
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:02,891
[Light] So, the price for receiving
the eyes of a Shinigami

36
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,310
is no more than half
of my remaining lifespan?

37
00:03:06,228 --> 00:03:07,187
That's it, right?

38
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:08,772
Yes.

39
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:11,650
Well then, do we have a deal or not?

40
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:13,735
Ryuk.

41
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:19,199
This deal is out of the question.

42
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:20,325
Huh?

43
00:03:25,789 --> 00:03:29,042
[dog barking in the distance]

44
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:33,296
[Light] Let's get this straight.

45
00:03:33,505 --> 00:03:37,217
My plan is to create an ideal new world
free from evil and all criminals,

46
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:40,721
and I intend to reign as a god
in that world for a very long time.

47
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:43,932
[Light] I might consider the deal
if it lengthened my life,

48
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,726
but not if I die sooner.

49
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,563
I figured you of all people
should know I wouldn't take this deal.

50
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:54,067
Yeah. I still felt I should tell you
that the deal existed, just in case.

51
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:56,194
Anyway, I've done my part.

52
00:03:56,278 --> 00:03:59,156
I don't need you complaining
I didn't tell you this earlier on.

53
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:02,033
[Light] This is what you call
"telling me early on"?

54
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:04,244
Don't you think you're a little late?

55
00:04:04,536 --> 00:04:06,997
I don't see why you couldn't have
told me this when we met.

56
00:04:07,664 --> 00:04:08,665
Or better yet,

57
00:04:08,749 --> 00:04:11,543
you could've simply included it
in the instructions for the Death Note.

58
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:13,003
Uh, good point.

59
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:17,549
He's not the slightest bit daunted
by the fact that I'm a Shinigami.

60
00:04:17,758 --> 00:04:22,095
He doesn't suck up to me, and he seems
to have no problem giving me a hard time.

61
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:28,477
-[Light] Well?
-Huh?

62
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:31,521
You sure there's nothing else
you want to tell me "ahead of time,"

63
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:33,523
Shinigami?

64
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,984
No, nothing else.

65
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:37,402
Uh, probably.

66
00:04:37,861 --> 00:04:41,156
-Really? That's too bad.
-What do ya mean?

67
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:43,825
You know, Ryuk, I might've seriously
considered the deal

68
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:45,911
if you'd offered me wings instead of eyes.

69
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:49,748
Just the idea of flying around
freely in the sky sounds very god-like.

70
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:53,960
After all, it's been mankind's dream
since antiquity to be able to fly.

71
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,756
You'd stand out if you sprouted wings
and flew around.

72
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:00,675
Not to mention the police would have
no trouble finding you.

73
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:02,427
I was only joking.

74
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:06,890
Anyway, if I keep bargaining for eyes
and wings and whatever else,

75
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:10,018
next thing you know I'm going to end up
becoming a real Shinigami.

76
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,772
Though who knows?
I bet that could be pretty interesting.

77
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:15,816
I wouldn't worry.

78
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:20,904
Even without the eyes and the wings,
you're already a worthy Shinigami.

79
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:25,992
[Ryuk] The Shinigami Realm
is slowly rotting.

80
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:28,787
We lead meaningless and empty lives.

81
00:05:29,204 --> 00:05:31,456
And the only reason
we still take human lives

82
00:05:31,623 --> 00:05:34,209
is because we're afraid to die ourselves.

83
00:05:34,918 --> 00:05:38,338
The truth of the matter is, we no longer
even know why we exist.

84
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:42,467
In fact, I doubt there's any reason
for our existence at all.

85
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:46,346
What I'm saying is, compared to that,

86
00:05:46,596 --> 00:05:49,099
you're becoming
a much more impressive Shinigami.

87
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:51,977
I don't know about that.
From what you're telling me,

88
00:05:52,102 --> 00:05:54,604
it sounds like I'm doing
a lot more work than they are, but...

89
00:05:55,438 --> 00:05:57,858
I don't want to be compared
to a Shinigami.

90
00:05:58,441 --> 00:06:00,151
I'm a human using this Death Note

91
00:06:00,235 --> 00:06:02,737
to make the world a better place
for other humans.

92
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:08,076
[Light] But I wouldn't necessarily say
that the Shinigami realm

93
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:09,870
is meaningless to humans either.

94
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:13,623
-Huh? Why do you say that?
-Well, just think about it.

95
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:16,751
Whenever a Shinigami like you
comes to the Human World

96
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:19,546
once every hundred, no,
more like every thousand years,

97
00:06:19,671 --> 00:06:21,631
the Human World changes dramatically.

98
00:06:22,299 --> 00:06:25,677
The existence of the Shinigami Realm
is extremely significant.

99
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:27,137
[Ryuk] Really?

100
00:06:27,596 --> 00:06:29,848
[Light] You told me just now
that the Shinigami realm

101
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:31,141
is slowly rotting, right?

102
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:33,310
Well, when you return from this world,

103
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:36,229
why not use what you've learned here
to try and change it for the better?

104
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:40,984
Well, Light, I'm not sure
why I never noticed this until now

105
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,986
but you're quite the positive thinker.

106
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:46,197
[scoffs] Yeah, of course I am.

107
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:49,159
That's why I'm using the Death Note
to create a better world.

108
00:06:49,326 --> 00:06:52,412
You have to be a positive thinker
to even attempt something like this.

109
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:54,164
[gasps]

110
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:56,583
[Light] That's it!

111
00:06:58,043 --> 00:06:59,044
I got it!

112
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:01,463
Got what? What's this about?

113
00:07:04,341 --> 00:07:05,550
I think I just figured out

114
00:07:05,634 --> 00:07:08,178
how to find the name of the guy
who was following me today.

115
00:07:08,428 --> 00:07:09,679
How are you gonna do that?

116
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:12,474
[Light] I'm gonna use the rules
of the Death Note to my advantage.

117
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,851
I already know that if I write down
a cause of death,

118
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:16,394
I've got six minutes and forty seconds

119
00:07:16,478 --> 00:07:18,730
to record the conditions
and exact time of death.

120
00:07:19,773 --> 00:07:22,192
First, I need to know
exactly how far I can go

121
00:07:22,275 --> 00:07:24,194
in terms of specifying
the details of death.

122
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:26,613
This should be interesting.

123
00:07:26,947 --> 00:07:29,616
THE FOLLOWING MORNING

124
00:07:29,908 --> 00:07:31,534
[phone ringing]

125
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:33,662
Yeah, it's me.

126
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:37,749
Another six inmates
were found dead last night?

127
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,918
All were heart attacks?

128
00:07:40,377 --> 00:07:41,336
It's him.

129
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,421
-What?
-Huh?

130
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:45,465
Bizarre behavior before they died?

131
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:46,758
Could you be more specific?

132
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,301
What do you mean?

133
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:50,512
So they didn't just die
from heart attacks.

134
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:53,181
No, what I'm saying
is they all died of heart attacks,

135
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,599
but it wasn't quite that simple.

136
00:07:55,100 --> 00:07:56,226
Before one of them died,

137
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:59,354
he drew a pentagram on the wall
of his cell using his own blood.

138
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:02,607
Another left a letter, but it doesn't seem
to be a will or anything meaningful.

139
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:05,485
And as for the third victim,
he escaped from his cell

140
00:08:05,568 --> 00:08:08,113
and ran all the way to the staff bathrooms
before he died.

141
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,322
[beeping]

142
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,328
[L] What is it, Watari?

143
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:16,705
Three more heart attack victims,

144
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:20,250
but the circumstances of their deaths
are different from what we've seen so far.

145
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:22,293
What do you mean by "different"?

146
00:08:22,877 --> 00:08:26,339
I'm sending you a copy of a letter
as well as pictures taken at the scene.

147
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:27,298
Okay.

148
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:33,221
[L] It sounds like he was afraid
that Kira would find him.

149
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:36,766
It's believable that our victim
might have been genuinely afraid

150
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:37,976
and wrote this...

151
00:08:38,101 --> 00:08:40,854
but we know Kira can control
the time of death.

152
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:44,357
What if he can also determine the actions
in the moments leading up to death?

153
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:45,483
In which case...

154
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:47,777
[L] Chief!

155
00:08:48,111 --> 00:08:49,070
Huh?

156
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:53,116
[L] We can't release details
of these men's deaths to the media.

157
00:08:53,241 --> 00:08:55,952
As far as they're concerned,
these are just heart attacks.

158
00:08:57,328 --> 00:09:00,665
I have reason to believe that Kira
was performing some kind of test

159
00:09:00,749 --> 00:09:01,875
using these criminals.

160
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,043
And if that's the case,

161
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:06,254
we'd only be giving him the results
of this information if we go public.

162
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,965
[Soichiro] Right, I understand.

163
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,552
So now he's experimenting on his victims?

164
00:09:12,677 --> 00:09:13,636
Horrible.

165
00:09:13,762 --> 00:09:17,390
He's playing with people's lives,
as if all this was just a game.

166
00:09:17,515 --> 00:09:18,725
It's unforgivable.

167
00:09:21,019 --> 00:09:25,106
[L] If Kira is really using criminals
as test subjects...

168
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:27,442
what is he trying to achieve?

169
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:30,820
[clicking]

170
00:09:34,783 --> 00:09:36,034
Look at this, Ryuk.

171
00:09:36,493 --> 00:09:37,660
I think we're in luck.

172
00:09:37,786 --> 00:09:39,370
The results of yesterday's little "test"

173
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:41,623
have already been downloaded
onto my dad's computer.

174
00:09:41,754 --> 00:09:42,832
KEITO NAWARAMI: KIDNAPPING, MURDER

175
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:44,375
These results are just as I expected.

176
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,503
The Death Note will work
for what I have in mind.

177
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:47,921
What do you mean by that?

178
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:50,048
One of them escaped
and ran into the bathroom

179
00:09:50,131 --> 00:09:52,008
I had specified in the Death Note.

180
00:09:52,175 --> 00:09:55,011
Another one drew the same symbol I'd
drawn in the Death Note before he died.

181
00:09:55,095 --> 00:09:56,429
TAMIKI: HEART ATTACK
ESCAPES FROM CELL. DIED 6:00 P.M.

182
00:09:56,513 --> 00:09:59,474
A third wrote the same letter I had
written in the Death Note. Word for word.

183
00:09:59,557 --> 00:10:01,184
LORD HAVE MERCY
I'LL BE HANGED OR KILLED BY KIRA.

184
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:05,188
All three did exactly
what I intended them to do.

185
00:10:05,897 --> 00:10:07,273
[Light] For the other three inmates,

186
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,984
I purposely wrote conditions
that were virtually impossible.

187
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:10,944
Huh?

188
00:10:11,308 --> 00:10:12,960
YUZO FURA: DIES IN FRONT OF
THE EIFFEL TOWER TODAY AT 6:00 P.M.

189
00:10:13,010 --> 00:10:16,032
With the first one, I wrote that he'd die
in front of the Eiffel Tower in one hour.

190
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:20,036
However, everyone knows it's physically
impossible to go from a prison in Japan

191
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,871
to Paris, France in only one hour.

192
00:10:22,247 --> 00:10:25,458
Since this couldn't happen, he simply died
of a heart attack in prison.

193
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:28,545
The next was supposed to draw
an exact picture of L's face

194
00:10:28,628 --> 00:10:29,629
on the prison wall.

195
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,256
KABEOKA: HEART ATTACK
DRAWS EXACT IMAGE OF L'S FACE

196
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:34,217
This also didn't happen. You can't draw
someone you've never seen, right?

197
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:35,760
[Ryuk] Makes sense.

198
00:10:35,991 --> 00:10:36,968
SHINSHIRO YAMAMAE: HEART ATTACK

199
00:10:37,053 --> 00:10:39,139
With the last one,
I tried something slightly different.

200
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:41,099
I specified that he'd write
a note that read,

201
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:44,060
"I know that L is suspicious
of the Japanese police."

202
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,980
To be honest,
I actually expected this one to work,

203
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:48,523
but it didn't end up happening.

204
00:10:48,815 --> 00:10:51,609
Which means, it's impossible
to make someone write

205
00:10:51,693 --> 00:10:53,069
what they don't already know.

206
00:10:53,278 --> 00:10:54,362
Or at the very least,

207
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:57,407
it has to be the kind of thing
they could come up with on their own.

208
00:10:57,490 --> 00:11:00,201
Basically, even the Death Note
can't do the impossible.

209
00:11:00,702 --> 00:11:03,413
But, as long as it's within
the realistic limits

210
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:05,165
of what that person might do,

211
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:08,459
I can control them as much as I want
before they die.

212
00:11:09,294 --> 00:11:10,295
That's very clever.

213
00:11:11,004 --> 00:11:14,132
But what's all this leading to?
What's the point?

214
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:18,595
These latest victims will no doubt
keep L and the police guessing.

215
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,305
Even as we speak,

216
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:23,433
he's probably trying to decipher
all the clues I left for him.

217
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:24,976
Especially that little note.

218
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:28,938
That absolutely meaningless dying message.

219
00:11:31,482 --> 00:11:35,236
[L] If Kira used those criminals
to conduct an experiment of some sort,

220
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,906
it means he's about to start something.

221
00:11:38,498 --> 00:11:40,615
If he moves now, there's a good chance

222
00:11:40,715 --> 00:11:43,953
the FBI will notice someone
acting suspiciously.

223
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:47,790
But perhaps he has a different goal
in mind altogether.

224
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:52,795
Could the pentagram and this letter
be some kind of message?

225
00:11:53,504 --> 00:11:56,007
[gasps] Is this it?

226
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,717
L, DO YOU KNOW?

227
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,552
Alright. Time for the real thing.

228
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:00,595
The real thing?

229
00:12:00,762 --> 00:12:02,597
Yesterday on the news,
they said this drug addict

230
00:12:02,764 --> 00:12:04,599
tried to rob a bank but was unsuccessful.

231
00:12:04,705 --> 00:12:06,100
WANTED CRIMINAL
KIICHIRO OSOREDA

232
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:09,103
He attacked a few people and then
ran away empty-handed. I'll use him.

233
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:12,357
It's kinda last minute,
but I'm sure I can find someone.

234
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:14,525
[Light] I got a few people in mind.

235
00:12:14,776 --> 00:12:16,736
A few people? For what?

236
00:12:16,903 --> 00:12:21,991
You'll see. Believe it or not,
I'm actually a rather popular guy, Ryuk.

237
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:25,536
[phone ringing]

238
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:30,500
[phone continues ringing]

239
00:12:31,334 --> 00:12:32,377
Hello?

240
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:35,797
Uh huh, Light? Morning.

241
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,527
[indistinct chatter]

242
00:13:05,535 --> 00:13:07,412
[Light] He's still following me.

243
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:08,705
Perfect.

244
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:12,792
This whole thing would just be
a waste of time if he wasn't tailing me.

245
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:16,296
[bus engine chugging]

246
00:13:17,255 --> 00:13:18,256
Huh?

247
00:13:18,715 --> 00:13:19,716
Light!

248
00:13:21,009 --> 00:13:22,593
-A date?
-Yeah.

249
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:25,430
-[giggles]
-It's a date no matter how you look at it.

250
00:13:25,722 --> 00:13:28,474
And I'm sure even my stalker
will see it that way.

251
00:13:28,683 --> 00:13:30,435
But this isn't just a date, is it?

252
00:13:30,977 --> 00:13:34,230
You said that you'd figured out a way
to find your stalker's name.

253
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:36,983
So, tell me, what do you plan on doing?

254
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:40,570
Huh? Come on. Didn't you see
what I wrote in the Death Note?

255
00:13:40,695 --> 00:13:42,238
I explained it in great detail.

256
00:13:42,447 --> 00:13:45,533
No. Doing that would take
all the fun out of it.

257
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:49,203
In that case, just be patient
and watch what happens.

258
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,791
-Sorry, did I keep you waiting?
-No, not at all!

259
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,878
Anyway, I haven't been
to Space Land since junior high!

260
00:13:58,004 --> 00:13:59,380
I'm so excited!

261
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:01,799
And the best part is
I have you all to myself.

262
00:14:02,175 --> 00:14:03,134
Uh, yeah.

263
00:14:05,053 --> 00:14:08,598
[man] During the week, he goes to school
and cram school at night.

264
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:10,266
Dates on his day off.

265
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:13,186
A normal kid. Just a hardworking senior
in high school.

266
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,898
[man] Chief Yagami's son, Light Yagami.

267
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:18,608
No cause for suspicion.

268
00:14:20,777 --> 00:14:22,362
[bus door hissing open]

269
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,991
At any rate, I'll be done
with my surveillance today.

270
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:28,117
And that'll be it.

271
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:34,624
[Yuri] I don't get it, Light.

272
00:14:34,791 --> 00:14:37,835
Didn't you say you weren't going out
until entrance exams were over?

273
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:41,214
That was before I scored number one
on the national practice exams.

274
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:42,632
Ooo, you're such a nerd!

275
00:14:43,007 --> 00:14:44,133
[Yuri giggles]

276
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:48,805
EMERGENCY EXIT

277
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:09,826
[bus approaching]

278
00:15:13,246 --> 00:15:14,414
[door hissing open]

279
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:19,001
[Light] It's him! He's here.

280
00:15:21,546 --> 00:15:24,340
Seven passengers excluding him,
no one's in the way.

281
00:15:24,549 --> 00:15:26,092
Everything should go smoothly.

282
00:15:27,135 --> 00:15:29,429
-[gun clicking]
-[driver exclaims]

283
00:15:30,012 --> 00:15:32,181
Stay in your seats unless you wanna die!

284
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:33,558
[people exclaiming]

285
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:36,561
A bus-jacking? You gotta be kidding me.

286
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:37,979
Everybody, shut up!

287
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:40,898
If anybody moves,
I'm putting a bullet in their head.

288
00:15:41,524 --> 00:15:43,651
Alright, driver, you listen to me.

289
00:15:43,734 --> 00:15:46,446
I know you've got the number
for Space Land's office on you.

290
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:47,905
-Call them!
-Okay.

291
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,868
[driver] This-- This is Sasaki,
calling from bus 174.

292
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:54,328
Tell them what's going on,
and no tricks either!

293
00:15:55,163 --> 00:15:58,207
My bus has been hijacked
and he's holding a gun to my head!

294
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,375
[Osoreda] Gimme that!

295
00:15:59,959 --> 00:16:02,670
You heard what he said. Now you listen up!

296
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:06,424
Have a female staff member bring
all of Space Land's cash from yesterday.

297
00:16:06,507 --> 00:16:09,469
I know it's there. Have her meet us
two bus stops from the park.

298
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:10,887
And don't make me wait!

299
00:16:11,053 --> 00:16:13,973
If you mess with me at all
or try to get the police involved,

300
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:16,726
I swear I'll kill
every one of these passengers.

301
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,394
[grunts]

302
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:23,441
[Yuri whimpering]

303
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:27,278
[Light] Yuri, don't be scared.

304
00:16:27,445 --> 00:16:30,656
As soon as he turns around,
I'm gonna grab the gun out of his hand.

305
00:16:31,574 --> 00:16:32,909
Don't be stupid. That's risky.

306
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:35,077
If it comes to that, I'll take care of it.

307
00:16:36,996 --> 00:16:39,540
It's okay. We don't have
to pass notes back and forth.

308
00:16:39,624 --> 00:16:40,917
As long as we keep it down,

309
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,128
he won't be able to hear our voices
over the sound of the engine.

310
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:47,924
Do you have any proof
that you're not his accomplice?

311
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,050
Why should we trust you?

312
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:52,970
-Accomplice?
-Yes, I've read about this before.

313
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:56,098
The first hijacker comes in
like he's working alone.

314
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:58,643
Meanwhile, a second one
pretends to be a hostage

315
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:01,354
and stays in the very back,
just in case something goes wrong.

316
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:02,813
What's the matter?

317
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:05,233
You-- You really think he is one?

318
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,944
[man] I've-- I've no choice.

319
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,737
I'm sure Light Yagami isn't Kira.

320
00:17:10,238 --> 00:17:12,865
If he was, he could just kill this guy
with a heart attack.

321
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,035
Here's proof. Take a look.

322
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:18,871
[Light] FBI?

323
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,374
I see. L needed an outsider,

324
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:25,044
so he got the FBI to investigate
anyone connected to the Japanese police.

325
00:17:25,253 --> 00:17:28,214
His name is… Raye Penber.

326
00:17:30,675 --> 00:17:31,592
[Light] I trust you.

327
00:17:32,677 --> 00:17:35,137
And I guess for the time being
I won't bother asking

328
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:37,640
what an FBI agent is doing on the bus
in the first place.

329
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:39,976
-Do you have a gun?
-[Raye] Yeah, I've got one.

330
00:17:40,268 --> 00:17:43,020
[Light] So if it comes down to it,
I can rely on you, right?

331
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:44,480
[Raye] Yes.

332
00:17:44,689 --> 00:17:46,315
[Osoreda] Shut the hell up, you old hag!

333
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:48,150
You want me to shoot you right now?

334
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:49,860
[Raye] That's right!

335
00:17:49,944 --> 00:17:53,239
This guy, his face was all over
the local news just a few days ago.

336
00:17:53,531 --> 00:17:55,408
Some junkie who tried to rob a bank

337
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,910
and ended up killing three people
before he got away.

338
00:17:58,411 --> 00:18:00,162
He's extremely dangerous.

339
00:18:00,371 --> 00:18:02,331
[Light] We're safe. He won't shoot us.

340
00:18:02,415 --> 00:18:04,667
In fact, he's not going to do anything.

341
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:09,088
Don't move, you little punk!

342
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:12,842
What the hell is that?

343
00:18:13,301 --> 00:18:17,013
Smart-ass. You guys were planning
something back here, weren't ya?

344
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:19,098
Damn it. If he sees that note from before,

345
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:22,226
he'll find out that Light was planning
to jump on him and take his gun away.

346
00:18:24,526 --> 00:18:26,355
MINAMI PARK BUS STOP, 11:27
SPACE LAND BUS STOP

347
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:28,733
[Osoreda] Plans for a date, huh?
Stupid kid.

348
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:31,694
Gotcha.

349
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:39,368
Huh? [gasps]

350
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:41,454
Who the hell are you?

351
00:18:41,621 --> 00:18:44,040
You in the very back!
What do you think you're doing?

352
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,667
Don't mess with me!

353
00:18:47,585 --> 00:18:49,503
How long have you been hiding back there?

354
00:18:50,296 --> 00:18:52,798
What's this? You're talking to me?

355
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:55,468
So you mean you can actually
see me right now?

356
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:57,511
[exclaims] Stay there, you!

357
00:18:58,012 --> 00:18:59,722
You keep away from me, you freak!

358
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:01,682
This isn't good. He's hallucinating!

359
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:03,225
Everyone, get down!

360
00:19:03,434 --> 00:19:04,602
[all screaming]

361
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:07,730
Oh, I get it.

362
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:11,067
That little note that Light
accidentally dropped

363
00:19:11,609 --> 00:19:14,570
was actually torn from the pages
of the Death Note itself.

364
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:17,323
Since he tricked this guy
into touching the paper,

365
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:19,825
he's the only other one on the bus
who can see me.

366
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,619
That's so smart.

367
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:23,204
Get away!

368
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,039
[Osoreda yelling]

369
00:19:26,207 --> 00:19:27,416
Sorry, pal.

370
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:30,461
I'm a Shinigami, so I'm afraid
your bullets aren't gonna kill me.

371
00:19:30,795 --> 00:19:31,837
[screaming]

372
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:35,675
[screaming and gunshots]

373
00:19:36,759 --> 00:19:40,805
-[Osoreda continues screaming]
-[gun clicking]

374
00:19:41,097 --> 00:19:42,890
[whimpering]

375
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:45,518
[Ryuk] Anyone who touches
the Death Note can see me.

376
00:19:45,643 --> 00:19:48,646
I have to stay till the Death Note
is finished or I see you die.

377
00:19:48,771 --> 00:19:49,939
Whichever comes first.

378
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:52,817
And a Shinigami can't die from being shot.

379
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,528
I've said all these things
at one time or another.

380
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:58,364
Well, he is the top-ranked student
in the country.

381
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:00,491
Guess I shouldn't be surprised.

382
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:04,286
He even used this hijacking
as a way to get the guy following him

383
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:05,996
to willingly give up his name.

384
00:20:07,832 --> 00:20:09,625
Stop the bus! Let me off!

385
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:11,043
[brakes screeching]

386
00:20:11,216 --> 00:20:13,587
SPACE LAND

387
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:15,840
[panting]

388
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:18,467
[tires screeching]

389
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:39,447
[Light] Eleven forty-five on the dot.

390
00:20:39,739 --> 00:20:41,699
Everything went just as I planned.

391
00:20:43,325 --> 00:20:46,537
[Light] "Kiichiro Osoreda.
Accidental death.

392
00:20:47,288 --> 00:20:51,625
Boards the 11:31 Space Land-bound bus
near the eastern entrance to the park,

393
00:20:51,959 --> 00:20:54,670
holding a loaded gun
and attempts to hijack the bus.

394
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:59,175
He sees a horrific phantom
and empties his gun trying to kill it.

395
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:02,094
Terrified, he flees the bus.

396
00:21:02,845 --> 00:21:05,389
Immediately afterwards, at 11:45,

397
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:07,975
he dies when struck by a car."

398
00:21:15,149 --> 00:21:17,443
[Light] The Death Note never fails.

399
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:25,743
You will be next, Raye Penber.

400
00:21:30,295 --> 00:21:36,170
TO BE CONTINUED
